exports[`column diagnostics > renders representative diagnostic text and view models from packets 1`] = `
"Target: payment_status (output: Final Result)

Column Lineage:
- 1 source leaf column(s), 1 intermediate reference(s), 2 expression step(s), 3 CASE rule(s)
- Expressions:
  - main_output.payment_status: case when ps.last_paid_at is null then 'unknown' when ps.last_paid_at < current_date - INTERVAL '30 days' then 'needs_followup' else 'active' end
  - cte_payment_summary.last_paid_at: max(p.paid_at)
- CASE rules:
  - when ps.last_paid_at is null
    condition: ps.last_paid_at is null
    result: 'unknown'
  - when ps.last_paid_at < current_date - INTERVAL '30 days'
    condition: ps.last_paid_at < current_date - INTERVAL '30 days'
    result: 'needs_followup'
  - else
    result: 'active'
- References:
  - payment_summary.last_paid_at [column_lineage]
  - payments.paid_at [column_lineage]
- Source leaves:
  - payments.paid_at (table)

Row Lineage:
- 5 row lineage influence(s) were found on the column lineage route.
- Influences:
  - where: p.status = 'succeeded'
    refs: payments.status [row_lineage]
    effects: row_filter
  - group_by: p.customer_id
    refs: payments.customer_id [row_lineage]
    effects: grain_change
  - order_by: total_amount desc
    refs: Final Result.total_amount [row_lineage]
    effects: output_selection
  - limit: limit 100
    effects: output_cap
  - join: on ps.customer_id = cs.id
    refs: payment_summary.customer_id [row_lineage], customer_scope.id [row_lineage]
    effects: null_extension

Candidate concerns:
- where (possible): where may influence the row population used to compute this column. evidence: p.status = 'succeeded'
- group_by (possible): The GROUP BY expression may change the aggregation grain. evidence: p.customer_id
- order_by (possible): The ORDER BY expression may change which rows are returned when combined with LIMIT/OFFSET. evidence: total_amount desc
- limit (possible): The LIMIT clause restricts how many rows are returned. evidence: limit 100
- join_on (low): The outer join should preserve left-side rows, but it may null-extend or multiply rows depending on matches. evidence: on ps.customer_id = cs.id
- source_data_value (possible): Source leaf values may be incorrect and can affect the calculated value. evidence: payments.paid_at
- case_when (possible): The CASE branch conditions or result expressions may change this column value. evidence: ps.last_paid_at is null -> 'unknown' | ps.last_paid_at < current_date - INTERVAL '30 days' -> 'needs_followup' | 'active'
- aggregate_expression (possible): The aggregate expression may change the value and depends on the grouping grain. evidence: max(p.paid_at)"
`;

